climbs.name: Sport Mining
climbs.fa: Erik Hansen, John Madux, Sean and John Hansen

content.description: I usually lead this with just the bolts but you can place a tcu or small cam to lessen the run outs (Run outs are not bad). I love this climb a classic for the area, Climb it every time I'm up there.
content.protection: 7 bolts optional tcu or small cam. 2 bolt/chains and anchor wrap route.
content.location: ten feet to the right of Decision Time and 10 feet to the left of aspen arete, on the Long Wall.

content.description: Getting off the ground is the crux. This climb was free soloed by Boone Speed after we put it in and he said it was 5.8.
content.protection: 3 bolts to anchors. rap or walk off.
content.location: Left side of the Jelly Stone Wall.  Park at the same Pull outs for the west side crags. Walk down the road about 50 ft then go left up a trail to the to the wall. This wall is just south of the curse wall (North end) on the east side crags 1st tier.

content.description: The crux is going right of the first bolt if you go left the climb is a little easier. This route is named after a sharpe shin hawk flying over head during the first ascent.
content.protection: 4 bolts, 1 pin, to 2 bolt/chain anchor.
content.location: left most climb on the North Edge Wall. This wall is just north/right of Minni Glass Ocean Wall.

climbs.name: Satori
climbs.fa: Sean and John Hansen and others (unknown)

content.description: There are 2 cruxes the first is the start climb the roof and flake when you can stand on the top of the flake climb left past a bolt then strait up through horazontals finshing with a bolt (second crux) up a trough to the anchors. Amazing! We did a first pitch to this climb starting from the gound. Its 5.9 and uses all gear I do not recomend climbing this. Instead approach left of the Jelly Stone wall then continue up another short gully to the top of the Satori Wall. turn south (right) and walk 100 yards. on your right you will see some bolt anchors and chain that can hang down in the upper trough on Satori. Either rap to the starting ledge or continue walking south to the end of the Satori wall then decend to the the starting ledge and travers over to the big ledge, roof and flake. Enjoy!
content.protection: Small to medium gear 2 bolts. I recomend tcu's 0-3.
content.location: As you are driving north into Maryellens pass the boulder on the right look up and see the slab then continue up the road about 50 yards. on the right will be a boulder scree and no trees blocking the view look up and locate the roof and flake about 20 ft up from the ground and 50ft left of the south end of the wall. Continue up 50 more yards and park in the Right or left Pull outs.

content.description:
On the Pine cone Wall scramble up to the ledge with the big pine tree. At the left end of this edge you will climb to a bolt then up to black Y crack, take the Right line.

A bolt was added after the first ascent that is where the crux is but the climb is still runout a bit and gear placment is very tricky.

Descend rap route
content.protection: 1 Bolt, small to medium pro, 2 bolt/chains anchor.
content.location: Pine cone wall Left edge of the pinetree ledge, west crags.

content.description: crux is on the face near the second bolt. Our first assent was all pro and we were rained off at the crux so we added the bolts and finished the climb.

content.description: Hard Rock Minor is the first and only bolted line on the first carg of the west side crags (South end of west side crags), its on the Three Aces Wall.
content.protection: 9 Bolts with optional #1 tcu. 2 bolt and chain anchors. if you exit the crack left of the last bolt the climb is 5.10 and medium gear would be needed.
content.location: Continue up the road to the end of the right side crags there is an obvious turn out to the left close to the river and small turn out to the right, Park here. Walk up the road about 50 ft then go down and cross the river to an old road on the west side of the river. walk north about 100 yards through aspen until you are in a grove of pine trees. On your left there was sticks pointing to the trail but take the path of least resistance up to the three aces wall. the trail should take you right to hard rock minor. use this approach for all west side crags. just head north to all the other east side crags.

content.description: Not a good climb but I did an onsight first ascent on this one and the pro was really bad. The crux is where the crack ends and you have to climb aways to the horizontals for decent pro however Derik (owner of the provo climbing store) climbed this and cliped the last bolt on calico camo which did not exist for the first axcent and said it was'nt to bad.

content.location: Crack just right of Calico Camo on the pine cone wall. start on pine tree ledge.

content.description: P1 Start on a nice finger crack on a slaby smooth face. Go up the crack and to the left of a big roof, then continue strait up to the top of the wall. Belay at anchors next wall is short 30 ft climb up a crack just right of the anchors. P4 scramble up to the to wall then take your pick there are lots of climable cracks they just have a lot of lichen on them and need more trafic to clean up. Walk of to the north.

content.description: this was a great onsight first ascent I have debated on placing a bolt in the black streak let me know what you think.

content.location: about 20 feet to the right of Rain Delay start on an obvious angling left crack/under cling to a ledge then go strait up the black trough to another ledge. Fallow the left angling low angle corner the go strait up to an ornge steep face with cracks all over, above this is a green lichen face and crack angle right to the anchors. rap route.

content.description: Aspen Arete climbs the right most arete on the long wall start right next an aspen tree. The first ascent was done with pre placed gear, the second attempt I could not find the gear place ments and bailed left to sport mining. I will bolt this some day the middle face is 5.10 the upper face is 5.ll but you can gor right around to corner and climb to the top to avoid the 5.11 part. there is a spot you can place pro for a directional at the top of this climb and use the sport mining anchors for a top rope.
content.protection: small to medium pro.
content.location: 10 feet right of sport mining ot the right arete of the long wall. left of diving board chimney (5.4) climbed many times to access the top of these walls.
